I"´<p>Django custom templates are nothing but our good old python functions with one or two arguments. Â e.g.  , the filter Â â€<em>sessionâ€</em>Â Â will be substituted t with the variableÂ <em>â€œrequestâ€ .</em>The catch is these functions should always fail silently and should return something(preferably something meaningful).</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code># A function that brings food for me.
def Â bringMeFood(val, arg):
